obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line 3
  line `THE NORTHERN INDIA FERRIES ACT, 1878`
  line `A CT N O. 17 OF 1878 1`
  line `[9 th November, 1878. ]`
  line `An Act to regulate Ferries in Northern India.`
  line `Preamble. — W HEREAS it is expedient to regulate ferries in 2 [Uttar Pradesh, Punjab, the Central`
  line `Provinces, Assam, Delhi and Ajmer]; It is hereby enacted as follows: —`
  line `I. — P RELIMINARY`
  line `1. Short title. — This Act may be called the Northern India Ferries Act, 1878.`
  line `Local extent. — 3 [It extends only to Uttar Pradesh, Punjab, the Central Provinces, Assam, Delhi and`
  line Ajmer.]
  line `Commencement. — It shall come into force in each of the said territories on such date as the State`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, fix in this behalf.`
  line `2. [ Repeal ]. — Rep. by the Repealing Act, 1938 (1 of 1938), s. 2 and the Schedule.`
  line `3. Interpretation - clause. — In this Act the word “ ferry ” includes also a bridge of boats, pontoons or`
  line `rafts, a swing - bridge, a flying - bridge and a temporary bridge, and the approaches to, and landing - places`
  line `of, a ferry 4 [and “ Punjab ” and “ Ajmer ” mean the territories which, immediately before the 1st November,`
  line `1 956, were comprised in the States of Punjab and Ajmer respectively].`
  line `II. — P UBLIC F ERRIES`
  line `4. Power to declare, establish, define and discontinue public ferries. — The State Government may`
  line `from time to time —`
  line `( a ) declare what ferries shall be deemed public ferries, and the respective districts in which, for`
  line `the purposes of this Act, they shall be deemed to be situate;`
  line `( b ) take possession of a private ferry and declare it to be a public ferry;`
  line `( c ) establish new public ferries where, in its opinion, they are n eeded;`
  line `( d ) define the limits of any public ferry;`
  line `( e ) change the course of any public ferry; and`
  line `( f ) discontinue any public ferry which it deems unnecessary.`
  line `Every such declaration, establishment, definition, change or discontinuance shall be made by`
  line `notif ication in the Official Gazette:`
  line `1. This Act applies to the Lakhimpur Frontier Tract, and to the Sadiya and Balipara Frontier Tracts in Assam, subject to cert ain`
  line `modifications, see Assam G overnment notification No. 442 - GS & 443 - GS, dated 26th January, 1940.`
  line `The Act has been extended to the whole of Madhya Pradesh by Madhya Pradesh Act 23 of 1958 (when notified).`
  line `It has been amended in —`
  line `C.P. by Acts 1 of 18 83, 12 of 1891, 4 of 1907, C.P. Acts 1 of 1931 and 23 of 1937;`
  line `Punjab by Acts 20 of 1883 and 12 of 1891;`
  line `U.P. by U.P. Acts 1 of 1914, 29 of 1948 and 8 of 1960 (w.e.f. 22 - 5 - 1960).`
  line `Sambalpur District by Acts 1 of 1883, 12 of 1891, Ben. Act 1 of 1911 and Orissa Act 6 of 19 39; 15 of 1948.`
  line `Coorg by Coorg Act 6 of 1940; and`
  line `Ajmer by Act 6 of 1945.`
  line `Orissa by Orissa Act 23 of 1950.`
  line `2. Subs. by the A. O. 1950, for “the United Provinces, East Punjab, the Central Provinces, Assam, Delhi and Ajmer Merwara”.`
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O.1948.`
  line `4. Added by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
