  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  sourcePage 4
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line 4
  line `1 [Provided that when a river lies between two States, the powers conferred by this s ection shall, in`
  line `respect of such river, be exercised jointly by the State Governments of those States by notifications in`
  line `their respective Official Gazettes 2 ***: ]`
  line `Provided also that, when any alteration in the course or in the limits of a public ferry is rendered`
  line `necessary by changes in the river, such alteration may be made, by an order under his hand, by the`
  line `Commissioner of the Division in which such ferry is situate, or by such other officer as the State`
  line `Government may, from time to time, appoint by name or in virtue of his office in this behalf.`
  line `5. Claims for compensation. — Claims for compensation for any loss sustained by any person in`
  line `consequence of a private ferry being taken possession of under s ection 4, shall be inquired into by the`
  line `Magistrate of the district in which such ferry is situate, or such officer as he appoint s in this behalf, and`
  line `submitted for the consideration and orders of the State Government.`
  line `6. Superintendence of public ferries. — The immediate superintendence of ever y public ferry shall,`
  line `except as provided in s ection 7 3 [and s ection 7A], be vested in the M agistrate of the district in which such`
  line `ferry is situate, or in such other officer as the State Government may, from time to time, appoint by name`
  line `or in virtue of his office in this behalf;`
  line `and such Magistrate or officer shall, except when the tolls at suc h ferry are leased, make all necessary`
  line `arrangements for the supply of boats for such ferry, and for the collection of the authorised tolls livable`
  line `th reat.`
  line `7. Management may be vested in municipality. — The State Government may direct that any public`
  line `ferry si tuate within the limits of a town be managed by the officer or public body charged with the`
  line `superintendence of the municipal arrangements of such town;`
  line `4 [and thereupon that ferry shall be managed accordingly.]`
  line `5 [ 7A. Management may be vested in District Council or District or Local Board. — The State`
  line `Government may direct that any public ferry wholly or partly within the area subject to the authority of a`
  line `District Council or a District Board or a Local Board in the Stat e be managed by that Council or Board,`
  line `and thereupon that ferry shall be managed accordingly.]`
  line `6 [ 8. Letting ferry tolls by auction. — The tolls of any public ferry may, from time to time, be let by`
  line `public auction for a term not exceeding five years with the approval of the Commissioner, or by public`
  line `auction, or otherwise than by public auction, for any term with the previous sanction of the State`
  line Government.
  line `The lessee shall conform to the rules made under this Act for the management and control of the`
  line `ferry, and may be called upon by the officer in whom the immediate superintendence of the ferry is`
  line `vested, or, if the ferry is managed by a municipal or other public body under s ection 7 or s ection 7A, then`
  line `by that body, to give such security for his good conduct and for the punctual payment of the rent as the`
  line `officer or body, as the case may be, thinks fit.`
  line `When the tolls are put up to public auction, the said officer or body, as the case may be, or the officer`
  line `conducting the sale on his or its behalf, may, for reasons recorded in writing, refuse to accept the offer of`
  line `the highest bidder, and may accept any other bid, or may withdraw the tolls from auction.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1920, s. 2 and the First Schedule, Pt. I, for the proviso.`
  line `2. The words “and in any case where the said Local Governments fail to agree as regards the exercise of any such power they`
  line `shall exercise such power subject to the control of the G.G. in C.” omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
  line `3. Ins. in the application of the Act to —`
  line `The U.P. by the U.P. Local Boards Act, 1883 ( U.P Act 14 of 1883), s. 65.`
  line `The Punjab by the Punjab District Boards Act, 1883 ( Pun. Act 20 of 1883), s. 79.`
  line `The C P. by the C.P. Local Self - Government Act, 1883 (1 of 1 8 83), s. 44; an d`
  line `Assam by the Assam Local Self - Government (Amendment) Act, 1926 (Assam Act 8 of 1926), s. 43.`
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O.1937, for the following words: —`
  line `“and may further direct that all or any part of the proceeds from such ferry be paid into the municipal fund of such town;`
  line `and thereupon such ferry shall be managed, and such proceeds or part s thereof shall be paid, accordingly.”`
  line `5. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for s. 7A.`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 3 of 1886, s. 1 for s. 8.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  kind page
