  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  sourcePage 5
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line 5
  line `9. Recovery of arrears from lessee. — All arrears due by the lessee of the tolls of a public ferry on`
  line `account of his lease may be recovered from the lessee or his surety (if any) by the Magistrate of the`
  line `district in which such ferry is situate as if they were arrears of land - revenue.`
  line `10. Powe r to cancel lease. — The State Government may cancel the lease of the tolls of any public`
  line `ferry on the expiration of six months ’ notice in writing to the lessee of its intention to cancel such lease.`
  line `When any lease is cancelled under this s ection, the Magist rate of the district in which such ferry is`
  line `situate shall pay to the lessee such compensation as such Magistrate may, with the previous sanction of`
  line `the State Government, award.`
  line `11. Surrender of lease. — The lessee of the tolls of a public ferry may surrender his lease on the`
  line `expiration of 1 one month ’ s notice in writing to the State Government of his intention to surrender such`
  line `lease, and on payment to the Magistrate of the district in which such ferry is situate of such compensation`
  line `as such Magistrate, subject to the approval of the Commissioner, may in each case direct.`
  line `12. Power to make rules. — 2 [ ( 1 )] Subject to the control of the State Government, the Commissioner`
  line `of a division, or such other officer as the State Government may, from time to time, appo int in this behalf,`
  line `by name or in virtue of his office, may, from time to time, 3 [by notification in the Official Gazette, make`
  line `rules] consistent with this Act —`
  line `( a ) for the control and the management of all public ferries within such division and for`
  line `regulating the traffic at such ferries;`
  line `4 [( b ) for regulating the time and manner at and in which, and the terms on which, the tolls of such`
  line `ferries may be let by auction, and prescribing the persons by whom auctions may be conducted;]`
  line `( c ) for compensating persons who have compounded for tolls payable for the use of any such`
  line `ferry when such ferry has been discontinued before the expiration of the period compounded for; and`
  line `( d ) generally to carry out the purposes of this Act;`
  line `and, when the tolls of a ferry h ave been let under s ection 8, such Commissioner or other officer may,`
  line `from time to time (subject as aforesaid), make additional rules consistent with this Act —`
  line `( e ) for collecting the rents payable for the tolls of such ferries;`
  line `( f ) in cases in which the co mmunication is to be established by means of a bridge of boats,`
  line `pontoons or rafts, or a swing - bridge, flying - bridge or temporary bridge, for regulating the ti me and`
  line `manner at and in which such bridge shall be constructed and maintained and opened for the p assage`
  line `of vessels and rafts through t h e same; and`
  line `( g ) in cases in which the traffic is conveyed in boats, for regulating ( 1 ) the number and kind of`
  line `such boats and their dimensions and equipment; ( 2 ) the number of the crew to be kept by the lessee`
  line `for each boat; ( 3 ) the maintenance of such boats continually in good condition s; ( 4 ) the hours during`
  line `which, and the intervals with in which the lessee shall be bound to ply; and ( 5 ) the number of`
  line `p assengers, animals and vehicles and the bulk and weight of other things, that may be carried in each`
  line `kind of boat at one trip.`
  line `The lessee shall make such returns of traffic as the Commissioner or other officer as aforesaid may,`
  line `from time to time, require.`
  line `5 [( 2 ) Every rule made under thi s Act by the Commissioner of a division or the officer appointed by`
  line `the State Government shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before the State Legislature. ]`
  line `1. Read: ‘T hree months ’ in U.P. — vide U.P. Act 29 of 1948, s. 2.`
  line `2. Section 12 renumbered as sub - section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 4 of 2005, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 11 - 1 - 2005).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid., for the words “ make rules ”.`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 3 of 1886, s. 1, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 29 - 1 - 1886).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 4 of 2005, s. 2 and the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-6
  sectionNo (6)
