  title `Page 6`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  sourcePage 6
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line 6
  line `13. Private ferry not to ply within two miles of public ferry without sanction. — 1 [Except with the`
  line `sanction of the Magistrate of the district or of such other officer as the State Government may, from time`
  line `to time, appoint in this behalf, by name or in virtue of his office, no person shall establish, maintain or`
  line `work a ferry to or from any point within a distance of two miles from the limits of a public ferry]:`
  line `Provided that, in the case of any specified public ferry, the State Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, reduce or increase the said distance of two miles to s uch extent as it thinks fit:`
  line `Provided also that nothing hereinbefore contained shall prevent persons plying between two places,`
  line `one of which is without, and one within, the said limits, when the distance between such two places is not`
  line `less than three miles, or apply to boats 2 [ w hich do not ply for hire or] which the State Government`
  line `expressly exempts fro m the operation of this section 3.`
  line `14. Person using approaches, etc., liable to pay toll. — Whoever uses the approach to, or landing -`
  line `place of, a public ferry is liable to pay the toll payable for crossing such ferry.`
  line `15. Tolls. — 4 Tolls, according to such rates as are, from time to time, fixed by the State Government,`
  line `shall be levied on all persons, animals, vehicles and other things crossing any river by a public ferry and`
  line `not employed or transmitted on the public service:`
  line `Provided that the State Government may, from time to time, declare that any persons, animals,`
  line `vehicles or other things shall be exempt from payment of such tolls.`
  line `Where the tolls of a ferr y have been let under s ection 8, any such declaration, if made after the date of`
  line `the 5 [lease], shall entitle the lessee to such abatement of the rent payable in respect of the tolls as may be`
  line `fixed by the Commissioner of the division or such other officer as the State Government may, from time`
  line `to time, appoint in this behalf by name or in virtue of his office.`
  line `16. Table of tolls. — The lessee or other person authorised to collect the tolls of any public ferry shall`
  line `affix a table of such tolls, legibly written or printed in the vernacular language and also, if the`
  line `Commissioner of the division so directs, in English, in some conspicuous place near the ferry.`
  line `List of tolls. — and shall be bound to produce, on demand, a list of the tolls, signed by the Magistrate`
  line `of the district or such other officer as he appoints in this behalf.`
  line `6 [ 17. Tolls, rents, compensation and fines are to form part of revenues of State. — All tolls, rents,`
  line `compensation and fines under this Act (other than tools received by any lessee) shall form part of the`
  line `revenues of the State.]`
  line `18. Compounding for tolls. — The State Government may, if it thinks fit, from time to time, fix rates`
  line `at which any person may compound for the tolls payable for the use of a public ferry.`
  line `III. — P RIVATE F ERRIES`
  line `19. Pow er to make rules. — The Commissioner of the division may, with the previous sanction of`
  line `the State Government, from time to time, make rules for the maintenance of order and for the safety of`
  line `passengers and property at ferries other than public ferries.`
  line `20. T olls. — The tolls charged at such ferries shall not exceed the highest rates for the time being fixed`
  line `under s ection 15 for similar public ferries.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1886, s. 2, for the first paragraph (w.e.f. 29 - 1 - 1886).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 29 - 1 - 1886).`
  line `3. An explanation has been added to s ection 13 in the C.P. by the Northern India Ferries (C.P. Amendment) Act, 1937 (C.P. 23`
  line `of 1937).`
  line `4. So much of section 15 is repealed as provides for the exemption from payment of tolls of any persons, animals, vehicles or`
  line `other things exempted by s. 3 of the Indian Tolls (Army and Air Force) Act, 1901 (2 of 1901); see s. 8 of that Act.`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 3 of 1886, s. 1, for “auction” (w.e.f. 29 - 1 - 1886).`
  line `6. Subs. by the A.O. 1937 for s. 17.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
